Darkbox toolkit module, add some useful tools to use with darkbox

Syntaxes:
    1) (process or command) | darkbox_t -e [bs]
    2) darkbox_t -l color Ax Ay Bx By
    3) darkbox_t -b color x y w h [-h]
    4) darkbox_t -c color x y r
`
    1) Convert command output to darkbox commands.
        bs : Block size (in octect/character), default : 16
       WARNING: Do not always take care of mouse position or color (platform-dependant).

    2) Draw a line from A to B, uses darkbox commands.
       color : Use 'color' command format (1-9, A-F)

    3) Draw a box with coords x and y and weight w and height h, uses darkbox commands.
        color : Use 'color' command format (1-9, A-F)
        -hollow : Do not fill the box

    4) Draw a circle at (x;y) with radius r, uses darkbox commands.
        color : Use 'color' command format (1-9, A-F)

NOTE: Coords are zero-based.
